Learning Objectives
At the end of this project, you are expected to be able to explain to anyone, without the help of Google:

Understand the Incident Response Lifecycle: Identify and describe the key phases of incident response as outlined in NIST SP 800-61.
Develop an Effective Response Plan: Create a structured incident response plan that includes containment, eradication, and recovery strategies.
Assign Roles & Responsibilities: Define key incident response team roles and their responsibilities in mitigating security breaches.
Analyze and Document Incidents: Conduct a post-incident review and incorporate lessons learned into security policies and training.
Ensure Continuous Improvement: Implement strategies for refining the incident response process through regular updates and testing.


Requirements

General
Follow NIST SP 800-61: Cover all phases—Preparation, Detection, Containment, Eradication, Recovery, and Post-Incident.
Clear Structure: Include Introduction, Phases, Roles, Post-Incident Review, Conclusion, and References.
Defined Roles: Assign Incident Commander, Technical Specialist, and Communications Lead with clear responsibilities.
Actionable Steps: Provide specific detection, containment, and recovery strategies with best practices.
Post-Incident Review: Establish learning mechanisms to improve future incident response.
Submission Format: Use Google Docs, Office 365, or PDF, ensuring clarity and professionalism.
Anonymization: Remove sensitive information from logs, reports, and examples.
